<tr><td class="printline">
<span class="postbody">I heard there's a point cap that eventually unlocks.  Rumor has it when you spend somewhere between 1k - 2k in one camp, the system unlocks and any left over or future additional points earned can be totalled and used at any camp of your choosing.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
</td></tr>
<br />
<table width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
<tr><td class="printline">
<span class="name"><a name="11612"></a></span><span class="postdetails">#38:&nbsp;<font color=black><b></b> Author:&nbsp;<b>Mezrin Kortex</b>,&nbsp;</font></span><span class="postdetails"><font color=black></font></span>
<a href="viewtopic.php?p=11612#11612"><img src="templates/subSilver/images/icon_minipost.gif" width="12" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" border="0" /></a><span class="postdetails"><font color=black>Posted: Fri Dec 05, 2003 9:23 am</font><span class="gen"><br>
</td></tr>
<tr><td class="printline">
<span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Xixun wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">I heard there's a point cap that eventually unlocks.  Rumor has it when you spend somewhere between 1k - 2k in one camp, the system unlocks and any left over or future additional points earned can be totalled and used at any camp of your choosing.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Here's the way it works.
<br />

<br />
There are favor points which are camp specific.  You must have earned enough favor in one camp to see all the items in it.  It takes 1500 points to unlock any camp.
<br />

<br />
All points earned in ANY camp go to a common pool of points that can be spent in any camp.  You can only buy items of value equal to or lower than the favor in that camp.
<br />

<br />
Example:
<br />

<br />
You have:
<br />

<br />
1500 points in Guk
<br />
500 points in MMC
<br />
100 points in Tak
<br />

<br />
Total points = 2100
<br />

<br />
You could spend those points by buying four 500 points items in MMC or twenty-one 100 point items in Tak.  Points earned in a particular camp do not have to be spent there.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
</td></tr>
<br />
</table>

